<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,153,791]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,621,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Singaravel &amp; Singaravel, 2020" authorityName="Singaravel &amp; Singaravel" authorityYear="2020" box="[324,502,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,502,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Hishimonus adi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[511,599,621,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Distant)" baseAuthorityName="Distant" box="[816,1048,621,648]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phycitis">
<emphasis box="[816,939,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. phycitis</emphasis>
(Distant)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Dai, Fletcher &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Dai, Fletcher &amp; Zhang" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffractus">
<emphasis box="[1106,1249,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. diffractus</emphasis>
Dai, Fletcher &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having the aedeagal shaft: with lobe like median process in lateral view which is absent (in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phycitis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. phycitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or sharp thorn like on inner margin (in 
<taxonomicName box="[682,822,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffractus">
<emphasis box="[682,822,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. diffractus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), with subapical lateral lamellate expansion rather than apical lamellation (in 
<taxonomicName box="[401,524,729,755]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phycitis">
<emphasis box="[401,524,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. phycitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or no lamellation (in 
<taxonomicName box="[786,929,729,755]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffractus">
<emphasis box="[786,929,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. diffractus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and with apical gonopore opening whereas opens subapically on posterior surface in the later two species.
</paragraph>
